this isn't the way to handle it.

31
00:01:19,362 --> 00:01:21,552
We can't make the movie without him.

32
00:01:21,552 --> 00:01:22,652
Movie?

33
00:01:23,252 --> 00:01:24,952
Isn't this dramatic enough for you?

34
00:01:25,122 --> 00:01:26,752
I will finish this movie right now.

35
00:01:26,822 --> 00:01:28,552
- Leave! - Boss!

36
00:01:28,952 --> 00:01:30,322
It's about someone's life.

37
00:01:30,392 --> 00:01:33,122
- I said leave! - Please, grant him mercy.

38
00:01:33,192 --> 00:01:34,652
Didn't you hear me?

39
00:01:34,752 --> 00:01:35,852
I can't leave...

40
00:01:37,122 --> 00:01:38,552
without Mr Bong.

41
00:01:39,822 --> 00:01:42,152
Do you want to join him?

42
00:01:45,552 --> 00:01:46,652
You...

43
00:01:47,352 --> 00:01:48,522
deserve to burn...

44
00:01:48,952 --> 00:01:52,052
in everlasting fire, too.

45
00:01:53,752 --> 00:01:54,822
Get them.

46
00:02:12,352 --> 00:02:13,352
President.

47
00:02:14,352 --> 00:02:15,952
Ms Oh, what are you doing here?

48
00:02:17,952 --> 00:02:20,652
I have something to tell you.

49
00:02:26,452 --> 00:02:27,452
I...

50
00:02:28,392 --> 00:02:30,052
I lied to you.

51
00:02:30,652 --> 00:02:33,652
Mr Bong didn't use me or take advantage of me.

52
00:02:35,552 --> 00:02:36,552
I...

53
00:02:36,822 --> 00:02:38,762
seduced him.

54
00:02:39,652 --> 00:02:40,652
Ms Oh.

55
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:42,052
I...

56
00:02:42,322 --> 00:02:43,452
had feelings for...

57
00:02:45,192 --> 00:02:46,652
Mr Bong.

58
00:02:49,222 --> 00:02:50,822
What are you talking about?

59
00:02:51,552 --> 00:02:53,452
Why are you talking nonsense?

60
00:02:54,192 --> 00:02:55,652
How dare you threaten...

61
00:02:56,192 --> 00:02:57,752
Living with you...

62
00:02:58,192 --> 00:03:00,292
was very difficult...

63
00:03:02,652 --> 00:03:03,952
and boring.

64
00:03:04,022 --> 00:03:05,922
I just wanted to marry you...

65
00:03:05,952 --> 00:03:08,052
and live a comfortable life.

66
00:03:08,222 --> 00:03:09,752
That's the only thing that kept me going.

67
00:03:09,852 --> 00:03:11,952
That's when I met Mr Bong.

68
00:03:12,252 --> 00:03:14,652
I knew it would be the end of me if you found out,

69
00:03:16,052 --> 00:03:18,022
but I couldn't help myself.

70
00:03:18,052 --> 00:03:19,652
I am sorry, President.

71
00:03:23,322 --> 00:03:24,322
Ms Oh.

72
00:03:26,152 --> 00:03:27,752
Don't bet your life on something like this.

73
00:03:28,652 --> 00:03:30,222
Tell me now.

74
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:32,452
I will pretend this never happened.

75
00:03:33,152 --> 00:03:35,552
I will cut my wealth in half and give it to you.

76
00:03:36,252 --> 00:03:37,552
I will let you do...

77
00:03:38,052 --> 00:03:40,422
whatever you want.

78
00:03:40,822 --> 00:03:41,952
Tell me it's not true.

79
00:03:42,552 --> 00:03:43,952
Tell me it's not true!

80
00:03:44,122 --> 00:03:45,152
President.

81
00:03:45,452 --> 00:03:47,652
I am so sorry, President.

82
00:03:49,352 --> 00:03:52,352
But the person I really love is...

83
00:03:53,452 --> 00:03:54,852
not you.

84
00:03:55,552 --> 00:03:57,122
It's Mr Bong.

85
00:03:57,752 --> 00:04:00,752
President. Please spare his life.

86
00:04:00,852 --> 00:04:02,952
Please don't kill him.

87
00:04:03,022 --> 00:04:05,252
I will take responsibility for everything.

88
00:04:05,352 --> 00:04:08,052
- How... - Please, spare his life.

89
00:04:08,552 --> 00:04:09,552
How can you...

90
00:04:09,652 --> 00:04:12,222
How can you say something like that to me?

91
00:04:14,652 --> 00:04:16,952
You know how much I loved you!

92
00:04:19,652 --> 00:04:20,752
Boss!

93
00:04:22,562 --> 00:04:24,152
- Boss! - No!

94
00:04:24,252 --> 00:04:26,062
- No! - Stay with me, Boss!

95
00:04:26,152 --> 00:04:28,952
- Boss! Boss! Wake up! - This can't happen.

96
00:04:29,022 --> 00:04:30,452
Call an ambulance.

97
00:04:30,562 --> 00:04:33,152
- Yes, Sir. - Boss! Stay with me!

98
00:04:33,392 --> 00:04:34,652
- Boss! - No!

99
00:04:34,852 --> 00:04:37,252
Boss! Boss! Stay with me!

100
00:04:37,822 --> 00:04:38,952
Boss!

101
00:04:44,652 --> 00:04:45,752
Ki Beom.

102
00:04:47,452 --> 00:04:49,852
What did you do to my dad?

103
00:04:49,952 --> 00:04:51,022
Ki Beom.

104
00:04:51,652 --> 00:04:53,062
Let go and I'll tell you.

105
00:04:53,192 --> 00:04:55,852
Hurry up and tell me what you did!

106
00:04:56,022 --> 00:04:57,022
I...

107
00:04:59,562 --> 00:05:00,852
I am to blame.

108
00:05:02,852 --> 00:05:03,852
What?

109
00:05:07,062 --> 00:05:08,062
I...

110
00:05:08,922 --> 00:05:10,062
I am the one who did this to him.

111
00:05:19,452 --> 00:05:20,952
Let's talk in private.

112
00:05:33,952 --> 00:05:35,052
What?

113
00:05:35,352 --> 00:05:37,452
Ms Oh is in love with Mr Bong?

114
00:05:38,552 --> 00:05:39,852
Is that really true?

115
00:05:40,152 --> 00:05:42,222
Keep it down. We're in a hospital.

116
00:05:44,452 --> 00:05:46,252
Where is Mr Bong, that useless piece of jerk?

117
00:05:46,352 --> 00:05:47,352
Where is he?

118
00:05:47,552 --> 00:05:49,922
Are you going to go beat him up at a time like this?

119
00:05:50,252 --> 00:05:52,392
Your dad is in surgery. You need to be here for him.

120
00:05:54,052 --> 00:05:57,052
I didn't know something that hideous was going on in my own house!

121
00:05:57,352 --> 00:05:58,522
Ki Beom!

122
00:05:59,752 --> 00:06:00,752
Gosh.

123
00:06:02,352 --> 00:06:03,952
Are you serious?

124
00:06:04,022 --> 00:06:06,022
Gosh, it was crazy.

125
00:06:06,192 --> 00:06:07,552
It was unbelievable.

126
00:06:07,852 --> 00:06:09,322
If it weren't for Tae Soo,

127
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:12,352
Mr Bong would've been long dead.

128
00:06:12,452 --> 00:06:13,652
What about President?

129
00:06:14,022 --> 00:06:15,552
He still hasn't woken up?

130
00:06:15,652 --> 00:06:18,952
I heard he's either getting a surgery or some kind of procedure.

131
00:06:19,052 --> 00:06:20,452
I'm not sure which one.

132
00:06:21,452 --> 00:06:24,422
Anyway, you need to fix the truck first.

133
00:06:24,452 --> 00:06:26,392
I heard you will start selling food on that truck tomorrow.

134
00:06:27,052 --> 00:06:28,752
Yes. I should fix it.

135
00:06:32,852 --> 00:06:35,152
Because of his hypertension, it seems that...

136
00:06:35,252 --> 00:06:36,752
he went into a state of shock.

137
00:06:37,222 --> 00:06:39,752
He had a ruptured cerebral aneurysm.

138
00:06:40,122 --> 00:06:42,252
But fortunately, he was brought to our hospital in time.

139
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:45,052
He only had to undergo a minor surgery.

140
00:06:45,552 --> 00:06:48,052
Dr Kim. Will my father be okay?

141
00:06:48,052 --> 00:06:50,652
He will be fine once he wakes up, right?

142
00:06:51,352 --> 00:06:52,752
We will know for sure...

143
00:06:52,852 --> 00:06:54,322
when he wakes up.

144
00:06:54,752 --> 00:06:56,752
We need to observe him for the time being.

145
00:07:08,322 --> 00:07:10,052
How dare you come in here?

146
00:07:12,122 --> 00:07:14,952
Get out. The sight of you disgusts me.

147
00:07:15,192 --> 00:07:16,222
Ki Beom.

148
00:07:16,452 --> 00:07:17,852
I know that I did something terrible.

149
00:07:18,652 --> 00:07:19,822
But...

150
00:07:20,052 --> 00:07:22,322
please let me stay beside him.

151
00:07:22,752 --> 00:07:24,452
You got some nerves.

152
00:07:24,552 --> 00:07:26,552
Do you think my dad wants to see your face?

153
00:07:27,922 --> 00:07:30,452
Leave while I let you walk out of here.

154
00:07:30,552 --> 00:07:32,552
I'm letting you go only because I don't want to make things worse.

155
00:07:32,552 --> 00:07:34,192
So get out now!

156
00:07:34,322 --> 00:07:36,052
I will go as soon as he wakes up.

157
00:07:36,192 --> 00:07:37,222
Please, Ki Beom.

158
00:07:37,292 --> 00:07:38,852
You really don't get it. Get out.

159
00:07:38,952 --> 00:07:40,152
- Get out. - Ki Beom! Ki Beom!

160
00:07:40,222 --> 00:07:42,752
- Ki Beom, please! - Get out!

161
00:07:42,922 --> 00:07:44,252
Ki Beom, please!

162
00:07:44,352 --> 00:07:46,022
Ki Beom! Ki Beom!

163
00:07:47,152 --> 00:07:48,222
Ki Beom!

164
00:07:50,952 --> 00:07:52,122
What am I going to do?

165
00:07:53,052 --> 00:07:54,452
Please!

166
00:07:58,052 --> 00:07:59,052
Dad.

167
00:07:59,252 --> 00:08:00,852
Wake up.

168
00:08:01,292 --> 00:08:03,452
You didn't know what a conniving witch she was.

169
00:08:04,152 --> 00:08:05,652
You said she was smart, beautiful,

170
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:07,322
and elegant. You made such a fuss over her.

171
00:08:07,422 --> 00:08:09,322
You loved her with all your heart.

172
00:08:10,292 --> 00:08:12,352
Look at you now.

173
00:08:12,752 --> 00:08:15,292
She really fooled you, didn't she?

174
00:08:16,952 --> 00:08:17,952
Get up...

175
00:08:18,122 --> 00:08:22,292
and say something.

176
00:08:23,752 --> 00:08:25,152
Darn it!

177
00:08:39,022 --> 00:08:40,662
You should've waited for me.

178
00:08:40,752 --> 00:08:42,922
Why are you doing all this by yourself?

179
00:08:44,392 --> 00:08:45,922
I heard from Sung Koo.

180
00:08:46,292 --> 00:08:47,452
How is President doing?

181
00:08:48,952 --> 00:08:50,852
He needs to gain his consciousness.

182
00:08:51,452 --> 00:08:53,662
Gosh, even so!

183
00:08:53,752 --> 00:08:56,552
How could you just leave like that?

184
00:08:57,052 --> 00:08:59,162
You're always getting involved in other people's business.

185
00:08:59,222 --> 00:09:01,662
A person's life was at stake. What else could I have done?

186
00:09:02,422 --> 00:09:04,752
Honey, I know it's in your nature...

187
00:09:04,822 --> 00:09:06,752
to help people in need.

188
00:09:07,162 --> 00:09:10,352
But what good is that if it makes things difficult for your family?

189
00:09:12,452 --> 00:09:15,552
Since a person's life was at stake, I will let this one slide.

190
00:09:15,852 --> 00:09:17,052
But I won't let it slide again.

191
00:09:17,852 --> 00:09:20,422
Do you realise what an important time this is for our family?

192
00:09:22,452 --> 00:09:26,422
I don't want you to get involved with Choongshim from now on.

193
00:09:26,752 --> 00:09:28,352
Thinking about what they made us go through,

194
00:09:28,752 --> 00:09:30,662
makes me shudder.

195
00:09:31,352 --> 00:09:33,422
- Okay? - Gosh.

196
00:09:33,662 --> 00:09:37,452
Don't worry. It won't ever happen again.

197
00:09:37,552 --> 00:09:40,452
From now on, I will only think about the food truck.

198
00:09:41,352 --> 00:09:43,752
From now on, I will only eat kimchi fried rice.

199
00:09:45,352 --> 00:09:47,162
You really know how to talk yourself out of things, don't you?

200
00:09:48,552 --> 00:09:49,952
Is there anything I can help you with?

201
00:09:50,662 --> 00:09:51,752
That's right.

202
00:09:51,852 --> 00:09:53,452
We need to fix up the truck.

203
00:09:53,552 --> 00:09:54,852
Thanks for remembering,

204
00:09:54,952 --> 00:09:56,552
but while you were saving someone's life,

205
00:09:56,752 --> 00:09:59,052
the children and Sung Koo fixed it up.

206
00:09:59,452 --> 00:10:00,752
They did?

207
00:10:02,052 --> 00:10:03,552
Do we need to move that?

208
00:10:06,422 --> 00:10:07,452
What else do I have to do?

209
00:10:07,952 --> 00:10:09,852
The weather is beautiful today.

210
00:10:09,952 --> 00:10:11,852
It would have been nice if I went and helped you.

211
00:10:11,952 --> 00:10:14,052
- It's all right. You stay here. - All right.

212
00:10:15,162 --> 00:10:16,662
I hope you make a lot of money, Dad. Good luck.

213
00:10:17,352 --> 00:10:18,952
You will be rich, my son.

214
00:10:20,122 --> 00:10:22,662
Let me know when you move locations, okay?

215
00:10:22,952 --> 00:10:25,552
Be careful not to catch cold, Mum. Call me if something happens, Dad.

216
00:10:25,662 --> 00:10:27,052
- Okay. - I'll see you later, Choon Boon.

217
00:10:27,122 --> 00:10:28,162
Goodbye.

218
00:10:28,222 --> 00:10:31,162
Here comes Soo Min's Kimchi Fried Rice!

219
00:10:31,252 --> 00:10:33,052
- Let's go! - Let's go!

220
00:10:35,552 --> 00:10:36,852
Bye!

221
00:10:39,352 --> 00:10:41,022
Earn a lot of money!

222
00:10:41,662 --> 00:10:44,952
Check on the production company often and keep an eye on Mr Lee.

223
00:10:45,452 --> 00:10:47,852
I'm sure he's still keeping in touch with that Mr Bong.

224
00:10:48,162 --> 00:10:49,252
- I'll do that. - Okay.

225
00:10:50,052 --> 00:10:51,162
What's that?

226
00:10:51,952 --> 00:10:53,252
President of Choongshim Construction.

227
00:10:53,352 --> 00:10:55,152
- Show your face. - Come out.

228
00:10:55,252 --> 00:10:58,052
- We want to talk to you. - Come out!

229
00:10:58,552 --> 00:11:01,452
- Let go! - He's the president. Move!

230
00:11:03,452 --> 00:11:05,492
Are you Baek Ki Beom, the president of Choongshim Construction?

231
00:11:05,552 --> 00:11:06,752
Sir, please go upstairs.

232
00:11:06,852 --> 00:11:08,352
What is it? What is this all about?

233
00:11:08,422 --> 00:11:10,252
I will tell you about it upstairs. Hurry.

234
00:11:10,352 --> 00:11:12,752
- Let's talk! - What are you doing?

235
00:11:12,852 --> 00:11:15,552
We're from Manbok Shophouse. There's something we need to say.

236
00:11:15,752 --> 00:11:17,652
Please, head on up. Security!

237
00:11:18,552 --> 00:11:20,352
- Sir. - We have something to say!

238
00:11:20,422 --> 00:11:22,652
- Mr Baek! Let's talk! - I have something to tell you!

239
00:11:23,052 --> 00:11:24,552
Manbok Shophouse will be redeveloped?

240
00:11:25,222 --> 00:11:26,552
It's my first time hearing about this.

241
00:11:26,952 --> 00:11:29,052
Boss started this project just recently.

242
00:11:29,252 --> 00:11:31,552
Why didn't he tell me about it?

243
00:11:31,652 --> 00:11:33,752
He said you were going through a lot of things.

244
00:11:33,852 --> 00:11:36,652
He said he would let you take over once it was settled.

245
00:11:38,952 --> 00:11:41,852
- What do those guys want? - It's about compensation.

246
00:11:42,052 --> 00:11:45,452
They think the compensation was too small.

247
00:11:46,052 --> 00:11:49,352
- They already filed a lawsuit. - They filed a lawsuit?

248
00:11:50,252 --> 00:11:52,352
There are always people like them.

249
00:11:52,422 --> 00:11:54,652
They always get in our way.

250
00:11:54,752 --> 00:11:58,422
I will take over this project.

251
00:11:58,752 --> 00:11:59,952
Bring all the documents related to this.

252
00:12:00,752 --> 00:12:04,152
Why don't we just do it our way?

253
00:12:04,222 --> 00:12:05,452
They are filing lawsuits...

254
00:12:05,552 --> 00:12:08,052
because we are being too easy on them.

255
00:12:08,392 --> 00:12:12,052
We could take care of this situation in no time.

256
00:12:12,152 --> 00:12:14,052
You idiot! We're not gangsters.

257
00:12:14,822 --> 00:12:16,552
We are businessmen.

258
00:12:17,452 --> 00:12:18,522
You're not thinking straight.

259
00:12:19,422 --> 00:12:20,452
I am sorry.

260
00:12:21,452 --> 00:12:22,552
Young Il.

261
00:12:23,152 --> 00:12:25,752
Keep a close eye on them and report back to me.

262
00:12:26,222 --> 00:12:27,352
And arrange a meeting with the lawyer.

263
00:12:28,422 --> 00:12:29,552
I'm going to take care of this.

264
00:12:30,252 --> 00:12:31,652
- Do you understand? - Yes, Sir.

265
00:12:31,952 --> 00:12:36,152
(Soo Min's Kimchi Fried Rice)

266
00:12:36,222 --> 00:12:39,752
Is it because the weather is cold? There's no one passing by.

267
00:12:40,222 --> 00:12:41,922
It's already 1pm.

268
00:12:41,952 --> 00:12:45,352
If we don't make money during lunch, we've wasted half a day.

269
00:12:45,452 --> 00:12:48,522
This is why I told you we should go in front of a school.

270
00:12:48,552 --> 00:12:51,552
They are on vacation. We won't be making money there.

271
00:12:51,652 --> 00:12:54,552
And they said a dish like this sells better around office complexes...

272
00:12:54,592 --> 00:12:56,322
because employees miss homemade meals.

273
00:12:56,352 --> 00:12:59,452
Is that right? Then let's wait a little more.

274
00:12:59,452 --> 00:13:00,552
They will come.

275
00:13:03,252 --> 00:13:05,152
- Welcome. - Welcome. What can I get you?

276
00:13:11,452 --> 00:13:12,452
Sir?

277
00:13:18,152 --> 00:13:21,652
What's wrong with him? Do you know him?

278
00:13:22,152 --> 00:13:23,252
I've never seen him before.

279
00:13:23,852 --> 00:13:25,652
He's a strange one, isn't he?

280
00:13:28,152 --> 00:13:30,752
You can't sell food here. Do you want to pay a fine?

281
00:13:31,052 --> 00:13:32,352
What do we do?

282
00:13:32,452 --> 00:13:34,552
Gosh, this is such a hassle.

283
00:13:35,352 --> 00:13:36,352
Show me your identification.

284
00:13:37,652 --> 00:13:40,252
All right. All right.

285
00:13:40,752 --> 00:13:41,952
I'm sorry.

286
00:13:42,052 --> 00:13:44,752
We didn't sell anything today so please let this go.

287
00:13:44,852 --> 00:13:48,422
You can't sell food here. We will get complaints.

288
00:13:48,522 --> 00:13:50,852
I am sorry. We will close now. I am sorry.

289
00:13:50,952 --> 00:13:52,752
- Please let it pass. - We are sorry.

290
00:13:52,852 --> 00:13:54,352
- I'm sorry. - Hurry up and leave.

291
00:13:54,452 --> 00:13:57,052
- Okay. - You can't block the street.

292
00:13:57,152 --> 00:13:59,852
We will move now. We didn't even sell one bowl yet.

293
00:14:01,252 --> 00:14:02,352
Ki Beom.

294
00:14:03,822 --> 00:14:05,352
Your father still hasn't woken up.

295
00:14:06,352 --> 00:14:07,452
Yes.

296
00:14:11,922 --> 00:14:12,952
Okay.

297
00:14:15,952 --> 00:14:17,152
Why are you still here?

298
00:14:18,152 --> 00:14:19,152
Although...

299
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:22,152
I did a terrible thing,

300
00:14:23,852 --> 00:14:25,252
I can't leave...

301
00:14:26,352 --> 00:14:27,752
President like that.

302
00:14:29,352 --> 00:14:32,952
I will stay here and repent my sins until he wakes up.

303
00:14:34,352 --> 00:14:35,552
When he wakes up,

304
00:14:36,452 --> 00:14:37,952
I will quietly disappear.

305
00:14:38,652 --> 00:14:40,822
I can't understand why you're doing this all of a sudden.

306
00:14:42,052 --> 00:14:43,652
When you did something like that,

307
00:14:44,652 --> 00:14:46,452
you must have known that this day would come.

308
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:48,152
Do Kyung.

309
00:14:48,652 --> 00:14:50,152
Please, let me meet him once.

310
00:14:51,352 --> 00:14:52,352
Please,

311
00:14:52,952 --> 00:14:54,422
let me meet him one last time.

312
00:14:55,152 --> 00:14:57,252
Meet him in your next life.

313
00:14:57,952 --> 00:15:00,652
Don't let Ki Beom catch you and put yourself in danger.

314
00:15:01,352 --> 00:15:03,052
You should leave for your own sake.

315
00:15:13,252 --> 00:15:14,252
Goodness.

316
00:15:14,952 --> 00:15:16,652
Why are we having a barbecue party?

317
00:15:16,952 --> 00:15:19,952
For you to work in the cold, you need to be strong.

318
00:15:20,052 --> 00:15:21,552
So you need to eat well.

319
00:15:21,652 --> 00:15:23,552
- I bought these. - Really?

320
00:15:24,222 --> 00:15:26,692
My Soo Min bought meat for us?

321
00:15:26,852 --> 00:15:29,822
How can I afford to buy meat when I get such a small allowance?

322
00:15:29,852 --> 00:15:32,552
He bought the meat and I bought the vegetables.

323
00:15:32,552 --> 00:15:36,052
- Gosh. - Help yourselves!

324
00:15:36,152 --> 00:15:39,422
Of course. My boy is so thoughtful.

325
00:15:40,552 --> 00:15:42,322
Let's eat. Let's eat, Mum.

326
00:15:42,452 --> 00:15:45,152
- Here. - Wow. Here.

327
00:15:45,252 --> 00:15:46,352
Let's eat.

328
00:15:46,422 --> 00:15:48,152
It looks delicious. Thank you.

329
00:15:48,252 --> 00:15:51,452
How many bowls did you sell today? 100 bowls? 200 bowls?

330
00:15:51,452 --> 00:15:53,822
Hey, it was just their first day.

331
00:15:56,452 --> 00:15:59,052
Actually, it turned out much better than we imagined.

332
00:15:59,452 --> 00:16:00,752
Our customers went...

333
00:16:00,852 --> 00:16:03,552
wild about our fried rice. Right, Honey?

334
00:16:03,652 --> 00:16:06,322
Yes, it was very popular.

335
00:16:06,652 --> 00:16:09,822
We will settle down soon. So don't worry about us.

336
00:16:09,852 --> 00:16:12,252
I hope it works out so that you can...

337
00:16:12,352 --> 00:16:15,852
buy me a mink coat and take me abroad, too.

338
00:16:15,952 --> 00:16:17,552
Gosh, Mum.

339
00:16:18,422 --> 00:16:20,652
Should we make a toast?

340
00:16:20,652 --> 00:16:22,552
- Okay. - Okay.

341
00:16:22,552 --> 00:16:25,822
To our health.

342
00:16:25,852 --> 00:16:27,952
- To our health. - To our health.

343
00:16:28,052 --> 00:16:29,852
Thank you. Thank you for the party.

344
00:16:32,652 --> 00:16:34,052
It's delicious.

345
00:16:35,952 --> 00:16:37,152
What's going on?

346
00:16:37,222 --> 00:16:38,752
- Come on, Dad. - What is it?

347
00:16:39,852 --> 00:16:42,852
You should get a massage. Take a seat.

348
00:16:43,052 --> 00:16:45,252
Okay. Thank you, Soo Min.

349
00:16:45,352 --> 00:16:46,422
- Goodness. - Here we go.

350
00:16:47,322 --> 00:16:50,152
- I will set it for you. - Gosh.

351
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:53,122
Does that feel good?

352
00:16:53,222 --> 00:16:56,552
It feels very good. Goodness.

353
00:16:58,252 --> 00:17:01,422
Soo Min! Why are you being so nice today?

354
00:17:01,922 --> 00:17:04,362
- Do you need money? - No, that's not it.

355
00:17:04,862 --> 00:17:06,152
I'm always nice to Mum and Dad.

356
00:17:06,862 --> 00:17:09,652
- Right, Dad? - Of course.

357
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:12,952
My kids are the best.

358
00:17:15,752 --> 00:17:18,752
This feels so nice. Gosh.

359
00:17:23,362 --> 00:17:24,752
Are you going over the numbers?

360
00:17:26,652 --> 00:17:30,422
Honey. We sold four bowls today.

361
00:17:31,362 --> 00:17:33,052
We were out in the cold the whole day...

362
00:17:33,822 --> 00:17:35,422
and all we earned was 16 dollars.

363
00:17:36,362 --> 00:17:39,452
When we deduct expenses, we won't have anything left.

364
00:17:40,552 --> 00:17:43,552
The family's so excited. How can we go on like this?

365
00:17:45,152 --> 00:17:47,252
Should we lower the price? Is it too expensive?

366
00:17:47,362 --> 00:17:49,452
But other places charge five dollars for a bowl.

367
00:17:50,422 --> 00:17:53,452
Maybe it doesn't taste good. Should we change the menu?

368
00:17:53,552 --> 00:17:54,552
Gosh.

369
00:17:54,652 --> 00:17:57,552
I haven't met anyone that didn't like your cooking.

370
00:17:58,752 --> 00:18:00,452
Then what's the problem?

371
00:18:01,252 --> 00:18:03,952
Gosh, this is only the start.

372
00:18:05,152 --> 00:18:07,052
It's not easy to do well from the start.

373
00:18:08,522 --> 00:18:10,052
It will get better.

374
00:18:10,452 --> 00:18:13,152
We will sell 10 bowls tomorrow and 15 bowls the day after.

375
00:18:13,252 --> 00:18:16,052
Then, there will come a day when we sell 100 bowls a day.

376
00:18:16,652 --> 00:18:19,952
Let's not expect too much for now. We need to look on the bright side.

377
00:18:22,422 --> 00:18:25,652
You're right. I just became anxious all of a sudden.

378
00:18:27,752 --> 00:18:28,862
It's okay.

379
00:18:44,362 --> 00:18:45,362
Ms Oh!

380
00:18:47,452 --> 00:18:50,862
Are you mad? How can you come here?

381
00:18:50,952 --> 00:18:53,752
I couldn't leave without you.

382
00:18:53,822 --> 00:18:55,052
Run away with me.

383
00:18:56,152 --> 00:18:57,252
Let's not do this.

384
00:18:57,452 --> 00:18:58,522
You and I...

385
00:18:58,862 --> 00:19:00,052
are already over.

386
00:19:03,152 --> 00:19:04,552
I thought you said you loved me.

387
00:19:05,952 --> 00:19:08,252
You even said so in front of President.

388
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:10,052
Well, that's...

389
00:19:10,952 --> 00:19:13,252
It was so that I could save you.

390
00:19:15,252 --> 00:19:16,652
Please, don't do this to me.

391
00:19:17,452 --> 00:19:20,252
I have to stay by his side.

392
00:19:20,452 --> 00:19:21,922
You call this staying by his side?

393
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:23,652
You can't even go inside.

394
00:19:23,752 --> 00:19:24,752
Even still,

395
00:19:25,952 --> 00:19:27,422
I can't leave like this.

396
00:19:29,322 --> 00:19:30,362
I'll regret it...

397
00:19:30,922 --> 00:19:32,252
for the rest of my life.

398
00:19:33,252 --> 00:19:34,452
I feel guilty.

399
00:19:34,922 --> 00:19:36,822
Please, wake up and smell the coffee!

400
00:19:36,862 --> 00:19:38,652
You might be in danger.

401
00:19:54,292 --> 00:19:57,022
Did you see that? Ki Beom just passed by.

402
00:19:57,122 --> 00:19:58,292
This is our reality.

403
00:19:58,362 --> 00:20:01,322
If he finds out that we're here, who knows what will happen.

404
00:20:01,652 --> 00:20:04,552
That's why you should leave right now.

405
00:20:04,552 --> 00:20:05,652
Ms Oh!

406
00:20:05,862 --> 00:20:07,952
Please, I'm begging you.

407
00:20:09,552 --> 00:20:10,652
I'll wait for you...

408
00:20:11,362 --> 00:20:13,322
at the terminal. Meet me at 12pm sharp.

409
00:20:13,952 --> 00:20:16,022
No, don't wait for me.

410
00:20:17,552 --> 00:20:18,862
I won't show up.

411
00:20:18,922 --> 00:20:20,652
I'll wait until you do.

412
00:20:21,192 --> 00:20:22,252
I'll wait for you every single day.

413
00:20:30,862 --> 00:20:32,452
Why isn't he waking up?

414
00:20:33,552 --> 00:20:35,152
What if he never wakes up?

415
00:20:36,052 --> 00:20:37,452
Don't say that.

416
00:20:38,522 --> 00:20:40,392
The doctor came by earlier...

417
00:20:40,452 --> 00:20:42,122
and said that we need to be patient.

418
00:20:43,222 --> 00:20:44,362
Dad.

419
00:20:44,652 --> 00:20:46,252
Wake up.

420
00:20:46,652 --> 00:20:47,862
You should get back on your feet...

421
00:20:47,952 --> 00:20:50,362
and get revenge on those who betrayed you.

422
00:20:50,862 --> 00:20:52,552
Doesn't it make you furious...

423
00:20:53,192 --> 00:20:54,252
to just lie here?

424
00:20:59,752 --> 00:21:00,752
Yes.

425
00:21:01,822 --> 00:21:02,822
What?

426
00:21:03,052 --> 00:21:05,292
The tenants sent in another petition?

427
00:21:06,052 --> 00:21:09,222
Do they want to see me go crazy?

428
00:21:11,552 --> 00:21:13,052
All right. I'll be there.

429
00:21:15,392 --> 00:21:16,822
What is it?

430
00:21:17,552 --> 00:21:18,552
It's just work.

431
00:21:19,152 --> 00:21:21,392
With your dad sick,

432
00:21:21,652 --> 00:21:24,022
you really need to take the lead and look after the company.

433
00:21:24,752 --> 00:21:28,052
You said that you don't want to be someone who just holds the title.

434
00:21:28,752 --> 00:21:31,292
You can live up to your title now.

435
00:21:31,922 --> 00:21:32,922
Of course.

436
00:21:33,052 --> 00:21:35,222
That's why I've been trying to be more responsible...

437
00:21:35,292 --> 00:21:36,652
and focused at work.

438
00:21:37,152 --> 00:21:38,252
You just watch.

439
00:21:38,422 --> 00:21:39,862
I'll show everyone.

440
00:21:39,952 --> 00:21:41,122
That's not what I meant.

441
00:21:41,492 --> 00:21:44,052
I'm telling you to rebuild your life.

442
00:21:44,122 --> 00:21:46,392
Forget the past and make an honest living.

443
00:21:47,922 --> 00:21:49,122
Don't forget.

444
00:21:49,452 --> 00:21:52,552
This is your chance to show Hyun Ji what an amazing dad you are.

445
00:21:52,652 --> 00:21:54,052
I got it.

446
00:21:54,452 --> 00:21:57,052
I'll take care of it all.

447
00:21:57,252 --> 00:21:58,292
Do Kyung,

448
00:21:58,522 --> 00:22:00,152
you're my wife.

449
00:22:00,752 --> 00:22:01,952
Take charge...

450
00:22:02,252 --> 00:22:03,652
and do what you want to do.

451
00:22:06,952 --> 00:22:07,952
The time has come...

452
00:22:08,522 --> 00:22:10,752
for us to spread our wings.

453
00:22:12,922 --> 00:22:13,952
(Soo Min's Kimchi Fried Rice)

454
00:22:14,022 --> 00:22:15,052
- Are you all right? - Yes.

455
00:22:16,152 --> 00:22:17,652
Welcome, welcome.

456
00:22:17,692 --> 00:22:19,052
Do you want some kimchi fried rice?

457
00:22:21,952 --> 00:22:22,952
Oh.

458
00:22:23,452 --> 00:22:25,152
You were here before, weren't you?

459
00:22:25,222 --> 00:22:26,452
What's the problem?

460
00:22:26,552 --> 00:22:28,652
I told you, didn't I?

461
00:22:29,052 --> 00:22:30,752
I didn't believe you, but you were right.

462
00:22:31,292 --> 00:22:33,922
When will you ever stop bothering us?

463
00:22:34,452 --> 00:22:36,122
I'm not sure what you mean.

464
00:22:36,192 --> 00:22:37,752
Are you running your own business...

465
00:22:37,822 --> 00:22:40,052
in front of our shops because we won't leave?

466
00:22:40,122 --> 00:22:42,552
I'm not sure I follow what you say.

467
00:22:42,652 --> 00:22:46,222
We know that you are the head of the gangsters at Choongshim.

468
00:22:47,552 --> 00:22:50,322
Excuse me, there must be a misunderstanding.

469
00:22:50,392 --> 00:22:52,552
My husband has nothing to do with them any more.

470
00:22:52,822 --> 00:22:54,822
Do you think we'll fall for that?

471
00:22:54,852 --> 00:22:56,222
You don't remember me, do you?

472
00:22:56,652 --> 00:22:59,752
Or did you do this to so many people that you can't remember?

473
00:23:00,692 --> 00:23:01,852
Do you know me?

474
00:23:02,322 --> 00:23:04,352
- Where did you see me? - Do you really not remember?

475
00:23:05,122 --> 00:23:06,552
Because of you, my dad...

476
00:23:06,652 --> 00:23:07,652
Stop it.

477
00:23:07,852 --> 00:23:09,192
You're wasting your breath.

478
00:23:09,652 --> 00:23:11,452
No matter what you do,

479
00:23:11,952 --> 00:23:13,652
we won't leave Manbok Shophouse.

480
00:23:13,752 --> 00:23:15,052
This is our home.

481
00:23:15,392 --> 00:23:18,252
We won't let you gangsters steal it away from us.

482
00:23:18,322 --> 00:23:19,652
Let me make myself clear.

483
00:23:20,222 --> 00:23:22,292
I won't let you do that to me again.

484
00:23:25,652 --> 00:23:27,452
Honey, what's going on?

485
00:23:29,452 --> 00:23:31,292
You stay here for now. I'll be right back.

486
00:23:31,352 --> 00:23:32,852
Where are you going? Honey?

487
00:23:33,452 --> 00:23:34,652
Honey!

488
00:23:45,652 --> 00:23:47,422
I need to be on my way soon.

489
00:23:47,852 --> 00:23:49,152
- Take care. - You too.

490
00:24:00,952 --> 00:24:03,052
- Aren't you cold? - I'm fine.

491
00:24:03,122 --> 00:24:04,122
- Hello. - Hello.

492
00:24:04,192 --> 00:24:06,322
- Thanks for the help. - No problem. We'll get going.

493
00:24:06,392 --> 00:24:07,452
- I'll see you later. - Bye.

494
00:24:07,752 --> 00:24:09,452
- See you. - It's so cold.

495
00:24:09,552 --> 00:24:10,952
Why did you wait outside?

496
00:24:11,022 --> 00:24:12,922
- It's fine. - Let's go inside.

497
00:24:13,692 --> 00:24:14,952
Be careful.

498
00:24:25,292 --> 00:24:26,752
Customers don't come out when it's so cold.

499
00:24:26,822 --> 00:24:27,852
I know.

500
00:24:32,152 --> 00:24:33,252
(Chul's Snack Bar)

501
00:24:40,252 --> 00:24:41,752
Go inside and stand by the heater.

502
00:24:41,852 --> 00:24:42,852
Okay.

503
00:24:49,452 --> 00:24:51,322
- Welcome. - Welcome.

504
00:24:52,252 --> 00:24:53,552
Who's the owner here?

505
00:24:56,052 --> 00:24:58,652
I'm the owner. What's the matter?

506
00:24:58,752 --> 00:25:00,452
I heard you wouldn't take our alcohol...

507
00:25:00,552 --> 00:25:02,152
because you already signed a contract with another company.

508
00:25:02,552 --> 00:25:05,122
Yes, they offered a better price.

509
00:25:05,192 --> 00:25:06,192
What?

510
00:25:06,252 --> 00:25:07,292
Then,

511
00:25:08,322 --> 00:25:11,392
how much do you think our protection fee is?

512
00:25:11,552 --> 00:25:13,852
You already ripped us off for years!

513
00:25:14,292 --> 00:25:15,952
I think it's enough.

514
00:25:16,022 --> 00:25:17,452
What did you just say?

515
00:25:17,822 --> 00:25:20,952
Watch your language, Mister.

516
00:25:21,052 --> 00:25:23,222
Should I make sure you don't say such a thing again?

517
00:25:23,292 --> 00:25:24,652
Should I?

518
00:25:24,822 --> 00:25:25,852
Please don't do this!

519
00:25:27,752 --> 00:25:29,152
Get off of him.

520
00:25:29,322 --> 00:25:30,452
Dad, are you okay?

521
00:25:30,552 --> 00:25:32,252
I'm fine. Don't call the police.

522
00:25:36,652 --> 00:25:39,192
You're the boss here, right?

523
00:25:39,422 --> 00:25:41,152
Please make them stop!

524
00:25:42,252 --> 00:25:43,652
I think it'd be best for you to leave.

525
00:25:43,752 --> 00:25:45,122
Please.

526
00:25:46,852 --> 00:25:48,292
You jerk!

527
00:25:49,022 --> 00:25:50,052
Look here, Kid.

528
00:25:50,422 --> 00:25:52,752
You shouldn't talk like that to your elders.

529
00:25:52,852 --> 00:25:54,452
Don't touch my son!

530
00:25:54,552 --> 00:25:55,692
You asked for this.

531
00:25:57,252 --> 00:25:58,522
Dad!

532
00:25:59,392 --> 00:26:00,652
Are you all right?

533
00:26:01,752 --> 00:26:04,022
Let's make sure this doesn't happen again.

534
00:26:04,052 --> 00:26:05,422
From now on,

535
00:26:06,392 --> 00:26:10,252
you'll only buy alcohol from us. Do you understand?

536
00:26:10,452 --> 00:26:11,952
Yes.

537
00:26:17,122 --> 00:26:18,252
We're done here.

538
00:26:54,192 --> 00:26:55,192
Tae Soo.

539
00:26:56,052 --> 00:26:57,052
Yes.

540
00:26:57,692 --> 00:26:58,952
What did you find out?

541
00:26:59,022 --> 00:27:00,152
Choongshim is planning...

542
00:27:00,222 --> 00:27:02,352
to redevelop Manbok Shophouse.

543
00:27:02,652 --> 00:27:04,122
They're kicking them out...

544
00:27:04,192 --> 00:27:06,292
but are offering a measly amount of compensation.

